NAME: Anirudh Veeraragavan

lab4b.c
- This is the C source code for the lab4b executable. It compiles cleanly with
  gcc and the usage for the executable is lab4b [--period=#] [--scale=[C, F]]
  [--log=filename]. Additionally the executable supports the following
  interactive commands: SCALE=[F,C], PERIOD=[seconds], STOP, START, and OFF.

Makefile
- This is the make file which supports the options default, which builds the
  lab4b executable, check, which runs an automated smoke-test, clean, which
  deletes all programs and output generated by makefile, and dist, which
  creates the distribution tarball.

README
- This is the file you are reading.

